I know it&#x27;s fashionable to hate callbacks, but I&#x27;ve never had a problem with them, particularly in a framework like Express.<p>The only time they can get a little tricky is when a db query depends on the results of a prior query -- but that&#x27;s what async is for.<p>So is this:<p><pre><code>  app.use(function(req, res){
    res.send(&#x27;Hello World&#x27;);
  });
</code></pre>
Really so much worse than this:<p><pre><code>  app.use(function *(){
    this.req.body = &#x27;Hello World&#x27;;
  });

</code></pre>
I actually <i>prefer</i> the former since you can see very clearly the request and response going in and out, instead of sticking it on the function&#x27;s context.
